    <searchtitle>NHS Business Definition: Oxford Orthopaedic Questionnaire (Shoulder) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
    <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_oxford_orthopaedic_questionnaire__shoulder_">Oxford Orthopaedic Questionnaire (Shoulder)</xref>
 is a type of 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_oxford_orthopaedic_questionnaire">Oxford Orthopaedic Questionnaire</xref>.        </p>
    <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_oxford_orthopaedic_questionnaire__shoulder_">Oxford Orthopaedic Questionnaire (Shoulder)</xref>
 is a 12 item questionnaire for completion by 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_patient">PATIENTS</xref>
 who have 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_primary_shoulder_replacement_surgery">Primary Shoulder Replacement Surgery</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_revision_shoulder_replacement_surgery">Revision Shoulder Replacement Surgery</xref>
 and is completed before the operation and at follow-up.        </p>
    <p>
For further information on the 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_oxford_orthopaedic_questionnaire__shoulder_">Oxford Orthopaedic Questionnaire (Shoulder)</xref>
 and the 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_person_score">PERSON SCORE</xref>
 values, see the 
              <xref href="http://www.orthopaedicscore.com/scorepages/oxford_shoulder_score.html" scope="external" format="html">Orthopaedic Scores website</xref>.        </p>
  </div>
